.Dd March 16, 2026
.Dt PIQLEY 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm piqley
.Nd process and publish photos to Ghost CMS
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Cm process
.Ar folder-path
.Op Fl -dry-run
.Op Fl -delete-source-contents
.Op Fl -delete-source-folder
.Op Fl -verbose-results
.Op Fl -json-results
.Op Fl -results-dir Ar path
.Op Fl -no-results-file
.Nm
.Cm setup
.Nm
.Cm clear-cache
.Op Fl -upload-log
.Op Fl -email-log
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a command-line tool for publishing photos to Ghost CMS as part of a
Lightroom \(-> Hazel \(-> Ghost workflow.
.Pp
Given a folder of exported JPEG images,
.Nm
extracts EXIF metadata including keywords, camera model, title, and
description from each image.
Images are resized according to the configured maximum long-edge and JPEG
quality settings, then uploaded to Ghost CMS as scheduled posts.
.Pp
Photos belonging to a 365 Project (identified by a configurable EXIF keyword)
are also sent via SMTP as email attachments after a successful upload.
.Pp
Deduplication is performed in two tiers: a local append-only upload log
(fast path) and a fallback query to the Ghost Admin API (self-healing when the
log is missing or incomplete).
This ensures that re-running the tool on the same folder never creates
duplicate posts.
If the Ghost API deduplication query fails, processing is aborted to prevent
duplicates; this is a fatal error.
.Pp
Posts without a title (no EXIF title field) are saved as drafts rather than
scheduled.
365 Project posts always receive a computed title and are always scheduled.
.Pp
Only one instance of
.Nm
may run at a time.
An advisory file lock is used; if another instance is detected, the tool
exits immediately with an error.
.Pp
Email send failures are non-fatal.
A failed email does not affect the exit code or the upload log; only the
email log entry is withheld.
.Sh COMMANDS
.Ss process folder-path
Scan
.Ar folder-path
for exported JPEG images, extract EXIF metadata, resize images, upload to
Ghost CMS, and optionally email 365 Project entries.
.Pp
Available flags:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl -dry-run
Preview all actions without uploading to Ghost or sending emails.
Prints a summary of what would be scheduled, saved as draft, or skipped for
each image.
.It Fl -delete-source-contents
Delete the contents of the source folder after a successful run.
The folder itself is preserved but all files and subdirectories inside it
are removed.
Has no effect during a dry run.
.It Fl -delete-source-folder
Delete the source folder and its contents after a successful run.
The entire directory is removed from disk.
Has no effect during a dry run.
.It Fl -verbose-results
Include successfully processed images in the result output in addition to
errors and duplicates.
By default, only errors and duplicates are written to the results file.
.It Fl -json-results
Write a single JSON results file instead of individual plain-text files.
The JSON file is named
.Pa results.json
and placed in the results directory.
.It Fl -results-dir Ar path
Directory to write result files to.
Defaults to
.Ar folder-path
(the input folder).
.It Fl -no-results-file
Do not write any results files.
When set, no text or JSON result files are created regardless of other
result flags.
.El
.Ss setup
Interactive configuration wizard.
Prompts for all required settings and writes non-secret values to
.Pa ~/.config/piqley/config.json .
Secret values (Ghost Admin API key and SMTP password) are stored in the
macOS Keychain rather than on disk.
.Pp
Run this command before using
.Cm process
for the first time, or to update an existing configuration.
.Ss clear-cache
Delete one or both local log caches used for deduplication.
.Pp
Available flags:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl -upload-log
Delete only the upload log
.Pa ( ~/.config/piqley/upload-log.jsonl ) .
.It Fl -email-log
Delete only the email log
.Pa ( ~/.config/piqley/email-log.jsonl ) .
.El
.Pp
When neither flag is specified, both logs are deleted.
The upload log self-heals from the Ghost API on the next
.Cm process
run; the email log self-heals from Ghost published posts.
.Sh CONFIGURATION
Non-secret configuration is stored in
.Pa ~/.config/piqley/config.json
as a JSON object.
The
.Cm setup
command creates and populates this file interactively.
.Ss Ghost settings
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It ghost.url
.Pq string, required
Base URL of the Ghost site, e.g.\&
.Li https://example.com .
Must not include a trailing slash.
.It ghost.schedulingWindow.start
.Pq string, required
Earliest time of day at which posts may be scheduled, in
.Li HH:MM
24-hour format.
.It ghost.schedulingWindow.end
.Pq string, required
Latest time of day at which posts may be scheduled, in
.Li HH:MM
24-hour format.
.It ghost.schedulingWindow.timezone
.Pq string, required
IANA timezone name used to interpret the scheduling window, e.g.\&
.Li America/New_York .
.It ghost.non365ProjectFilterTags
.Pq array of strings, optional, default: []
Tags that exclude non-365 posts from the schedule-date calculation.
Posts tagged with any value in this list are not counted when determining
the next available schedule slot.
.El
.Ss Image processing
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It processing.maxLongEdge
.Pq integer, required
Maximum pixel length of the longest edge after resize.
Images smaller than this value are not upscaled.
.It processing.jpegQuality
.Pq integer, required
JPEG compression quality on a scale of 1\(en100.
Higher values produce larger files with less compression artefacts.
.El
.Ss 365 Project
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It project365.keyword
.Pq string, required
EXIF keyword that identifies a photo as a 365 Project entry.
Matching is case-sensitive.
.It project365.referenceDate
.Pq string, required
Start date for day numbering, in
.Li YYYY-MM-DD
format.
Day 1 is this date (the day the first photo was taken).
.It project365.emailTo
.Pq string, required
Email address to which 365 Project photos are sent as attachments.
.El
.Ss SMTP
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It smtp.host
.Pq string, required
Hostname of the outgoing SMTP server.
.It smtp.port
.Pq integer, required
SMTP server port number.
Typically 587 for STARTTLS.
.It smtp.username
.Pq string, required
Login username for SMTP authentication.
.It smtp.from
.Pq string, required
Sender address used in outgoing email headers.
.El
.Ss Tags
.Pp
Before any tag configuration is applied,
.Nm
flattens hierarchical EXIF keywords to their leaf nodes.
Lightroom and other editors store keywords in a hierarchy separated by
.Sq ">"
characters.
Only the rightmost (leaf) component is used; parent levels are discarded
and surrounding whitespace is trimmed.
.Pp
For example, a photo with these EXIF keywords:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
Animals > Cats > Tabby
Places > New York
365 Project
.Ed
.Pp
produces the leaf set
.Bq Tabby, New York, 365 Project .
These leaf keywords are then matched against the
.Li tagBlocklist ,
tested for the 365 Project keyword, and \(em if not blocked \(em sent to
Ghost as tags.
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It tagBlocklist
.Pq array of strings, optional, default: []
Patterns to prevent specific leaf keywords from becoming Ghost tags.
Each pattern is matched against the leaf node after hierarchical
flattening described above.
See
.Sx Pattern Matching
below for supported pattern syntax.
.It requiredTags
.Pq array of strings, optional, default: []
Tag names always added to every post, regardless of EXIF keywords.
.It cameraModelTags
.Pq object, optional, default: {}
Maps camera model patterns to arrays of Ghost tag names.
When a photo's EXIF camera model string matches a key, all corresponding
tags are added to the post.
Keys use the same pattern syntax as
.Li tagBlocklist .
See
.Sx Pattern Matching
below.
.El
.Ss Pattern Matching
Pattern matching is used by the
.Li tagBlocklist
array and by keys in the
.Li cameraModelTags
object.
Three types of pattern are supported:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Plain string
Exact match, case-insensitive.
For example,
.Qq Canon EOS R5
matches
.Qq canon eos r5 .
.It Li "glob:<pattern>"
Glob pattern.
.Sq *
matches any sequence of characters;
.Sq \&?
matches exactly one character.
Matching is case-insensitive.
For example,
.Li glob:*Nikon*
matches any camera model containing
.Qq Nikon .
.It Li "regex:<pattern>"
Regular expression with full-match semantics: the pattern must match the
entire string.
Matching is case-insensitive.
For example,
.Li regex:Sony\es+a\ed+.*
matches Sony alpha model names such as
.Qq Sony a7R IV .
.El
.Pp
All matching is case-insensitive.
When multiple patterns match the same value, all corresponding tags are
accumulated and deduplicated.
.Pp
Example
.Li cameraModelTags
configuration:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
{
  "cameraModelTags": {
    "Canon EOS R5": ["Canon", "Mirrorless"],
    "glob:*Nikon*": ["Nikon"],
    "regex:Sony\es+a\ed+.*": ["Sony", "Mirrorless"]
  }
}
.Ed
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Pa ~/.config/piqley/config.json
Configuration file (JSON).
Created and populated by the
.Cm setup
command.
.It Pa ~/.config/piqley/upload-log.jsonl
Append-only log of successful Ghost uploads.
Used as the primary (fast-path) deduplication cache.
Safe to delete; the cache self-heals from the Ghost API on the next run.
.It Pa ~/.config/piqley/email-log.jsonl
Append-only log of sent 365 Project emails.
Prevents duplicate emails from being sent if the tool is run again on the
same folder.
.It Keychain service Li piqley-ghost
Ghost Admin API key, stored in the macOS Keychain by the
.Cm setup
command.
.It Keychain service Li piqley-smtp
SMTP password, stored in the macOS Keychain by the
.Cm setup
command.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It 0
All images processed successfully.
.It 1
Fatal error.
Causes include: missing or invalid configuration, Ghost API failure during
deduplication, and another instance of
.Nm
already running.
.It 2
Partial success.
One or more images encountered errors during processing, but the remaining
images were handled without issue.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
Process a folder of exported images:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
piqley process ~/Photos/export
.Ed
.Pp
Preview what would happen without uploading or emailing:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
piqley process ~/Photos/export --dry-run
.Ed
.Pp
Write a JSON results file to a custom directory:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
piqley process ~/Photos/export --json-results --results-dir /tmp/results
.Ed
.Pp
Clear only the upload log cache:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
piqley clear-cache --upload-log
.Ed
.Pp
Example
.Li cameraModelTags
configuration for matching camera models and assigning Ghost tags:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
{
  "cameraModelTags": {
    "Canon EOS R5": ["Canon", "Mirrorless"],
    "glob:*Nikon*": ["Nikon"],
    "regex:Sony\es+a\ed+.*": ["Sony", "Mirrorless"]
  }
}
.Ed
